<p class="indent2" style="-uslm-lc:I13" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">An employee (within the meaning of <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s5561/2">section 5561(2) of title 5</ref> of the United States Code) is in a missing status for any period for which he is entitled to pay and allowances under section 5562 of such title 5.</p>
